(22783, 24781, 2406, 1, 'Ride The Wind (single)', '這是Storyteller整張概念專輯中最早寫完的一首歌(大概去年六月)，很輕快的重搖滾，希望沒聽過我音樂的人也會喜歡。以單曲型態提前發行，試聽剛好斷在精采的\r\n吉他solo前，後面還有第三種型態的Chorus。喜歡的話請支持一下買回去聽。專輯版本後面還有一小段銜接用的橋段。', '2010-02-25 00:00:00', 2000, 20, 0, 1, 'Ride the Wind\r\n\r\nVERSE 1:\r\nJust another lonely day\r\nJust another boring day\r\nI wonder why the world keeps turning\r\nJust another nameless street\r\nJust another meanigless strife\r\nCan''t forget your words about the new world\r\n\r\nVERSE 2:\r\nOne must beleive to see it\r\nOne must be strong to face it\r\nIt sounds like me oh it''s so perfect\r\nOne must be so determined\r\nOne must be free of his mind\r\nLeave nothing behind\r\nHis new life\r\n\r\nCHORUS 1-1:\r\nFlying high in the sky\r\nI''ve dreamed of this long before\r\nascension of a man\r\nSpread the clouds\r\nNow gaze into the stars\r\nIt''s coming now\r\nIt''s coming over\r\n\r\nCHORUS 1-2:\r\nRight! Amazing lights shoot from nowhere\r\nThe vortex constructs a crystal gate\r\nRide the wind and seize the ligntning blades\r\nInto the new world a different(better) path (place)\r\n\r\nVERSE 3:\r\nNot another lonley day\r\nNot another boring day\r\nI am looking forward what the new world will bring me\r\nNot another sensless pain\r\nNot another souless plan\r\nI keep on fighting to test my own faith\r\n\r\nVERSE 4:\r\nI believe it so I can see it\r\nI''m strong so I can face it\r\nin the world full of surprise and danger\r\nUndoubtly so determined\r\nUnlimited imagination\r\nFinally I find my own place\r\n\r\nCHORUS', '', 300, '', 'vicnest', 'vicnest', 'vicnest', 'vicnest', '', 1, 0, 0, '2010-02-25 22:45:25', '2015-03-12 13:41:32', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(22784, 43808, 0, 1, 'Tellya in 5 Minutes', 'The Music for ''Tellya in 5 Minutes'' was written by Boston Paul over the summer of 2009. The Natives of Space breathed Life into it.\r\n\r\nBe sure to wear your Jazzy Peace Paint when listening to it...', '2009-07-31 00:00:00', 2000, 0, 2, 7, 'Just Music and Vocal Sounds for now.', '', 203, '', 'Native Space', 'Mike Mudd and Boston Paul', 'Refuge Music', 'Refuge Studios', '', 0, 1, 0, '2010-02-25 22:49:48', '2015-03-12 13:41:32', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
